            "question_text": "Find the coordinates of the points of intersection of C and D.",
            "solution_text": "Substitute \\(y = 2x - 5\\) into \\(y^2 + 3x - 2x^2 = 10\\):\n\\((2x - 5)^2 + 3x - 2x^2 = 10\\)\n\\(4x^2 - 20x + 25 + 3x - 2x^2 = 10\\)\n\\(2x^2 - 17x + 15 = 0\\)\n\\((2x - 3)(x - 5) = 0\\)\nSo \\(x = \\frac{3}{2}\\) or \\(x = 5\\).\nWhen \\(x = \\frac{3}{2}\\), \\(y = 2(\\frac{3}{2}) - 5 = 3 - 5 = -2\\).\nWhen \\(x = 5\\), \\(y = 2(5) - 5 = 10 - 5 = 5\\).\nTherefore, the points of intersection are \\((\\frac{3}{2}, -2)\\) and \\((5, 5)\\)."
